## 🔴 Chapter VI — Red Mist

At the moment the creatures seemed unstoppable, two columns of **dark crimson fog** boiled up from the floor and became men.

**Red Wizards.**

One of the wizards from Thay slashed down his forearm with a ritual dagger. Tendrils of his blood escaped from the long gash, writhing and hovering. Awaiting instruction. 
With a flick of the wrist from the gashed arm the blood lunged forward. Forcing itself into the eyes, mouths, and skulls of every vampiric horror in the room. One by one they were compressed. Crushed. Fell.

The other wizard turned and pointed — at each party member in turn — and they found themselves frozen in place.

---

## 👁️ Chapter VII — The Voice in Every Corner

From everywhere at once — the walls, the air, the space just behind each ear — something spoke. Not loud. Not threatening. Something worse: *knowing.*

The smooth and confident voice unhurriedly addressed the room...

---
*"Those old eyes... and yes, the moniker is there... the kindred."*


*"The out of place depth dweller... you belong in the eternal night."*


*"And you... you're watching the wrong sky, oh pious one... why did it take you away during the transition... very interesting."*


*"Hmm... how restless for perfection you are... we can bring back his spark together..."*


*"It is not wild. It only seems wild to minds too small to see the patterns."*


---

Silence. The Red Wizards thought they stood in complete control of what remained of the burning Clockwork Stein. The creatures lay in bloodied heaps, compressed where they fell. The five adventurers had no answers. Frozen, singled out, spoken to by something that clearly knew them better than they knew each other. And now something enormous had just turned its eye towards them all.

---

*The Curse of Strahd has not yet begun. This was only the road leading to the door.*

`End of Prologue · Session One · Neverwinter, The Blacklake District`
